communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

1. Any and all e-mails, memos, and other forms of internal and external communication sent or received by an employee of your office containing or referencing the word "re-sentencing" or any grammatical variation occurring between the dates of 1/1/2022 and 7/11/2024. 
2. Any and all relevant responses to the aforementioned communications.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

J

title: YouTube Priority Flagger and Trusted Flagger programs (Department of Homeland Security)

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Participation, including any (agency) staff training, in the YouTube Priority Flagger and Trusted Flagger programs;

Reporting history, logs, and other documentation in the YouTube Priority Flagger program and Trusted Flagger program;

Any records and/or documents pertaining to agency communication with NGOs (nongovernmental organizations) who are involved with the YouTube Priority Flagger and Trusted Flagger programs.

Information on the YouTube Priority Flagger program (formerly titled the Trusted Flagger program) may be found here:
https://support.google.com/youtube/answer/7554338?hl=en

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Susan Maret
